13:50.264 --> 13:53.136
Um, it was ill-advised,
so I ended it,

13:53.267 --> 13:54.834
but to be clear,

13:54.921 --> 13:57.793
that was long before
I reconnected with Sage

13:57.924 --> 14:00.317
and created our school,
High Water.

14:00.448 --> 14:02.754
But you continued to have
some contact with Mr. Octavio

14:02.885 --> 14:04.539
even after that time, correct?

14:04.669 --> 14:06.454
Yes, of course.

14:06.584 --> 14:09.022
He was the father
of one of my students.

14:09.152 --> 14:12.939
But the contact was minimal
and entirely professional.

14:13.026 --> 14:14.897
Professional. Yes.

14:15.028 --> 14:16.507
But around that time,

14:16.638 --> 14:20.250
did you procure
illegal narcotics

14:20.381 --> 14:23.514
from Mr. Octavio,
a known drug dealer?

14:23.645 --> 14:26.996
[tense music plays]

14:27.127 --> 14:28.693
I can explain that.

14:28.824 --> 14:30.826
Um, my prescription had
run out--

14:30.957 --> 14:32.523
Oh, okay. Oh.

14:32.654 --> 14:34.569
Now I'm confused

14:34.699 --> 14:36.658
because you said
that at this point,

14:36.788 --> 14:38.834
your relationship
with Mr. Octavio was minimal.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.488
That he was just a parent
of one of your students.

14:40.618 --> 14:43.752
Ms. Jones...

14:43.883 --> 14:45.841
did you not have sex
with Ernest Octavio

14:45.928 --> 14:48.800
on the High Water campus

14:48.931 --> 14:50.759
just weeks before
he was killed?

14:50.933 --> 14:53.675
♪ ♪

14:55.155 --> 14:56.983
It's a simple yes or no.
Ms. Jones,

14:57.113 --> 14:59.072
and I will remind you,
you are under oath.

14:59.246 --> 15:01.944
♪ ♪

15:08.211 --> 15:10.431
-Yes.
-[Erin] Oh.

15:10.561 --> 15:12.607
So that was after
High Water, then,

15:12.737 --> 15:15.262
because you just said
that you had broken it off

15:15.392 --> 15:16.698
with Ernest by then.

15:16.828 --> 15:18.918
[laughs]
That's quite a school

15:19.005 --> 15:20.267
you've got going on there,
Ms. Jones.

15:20.354 --> 15:22.443
Drugs. Wild sex.

15:22.573 --> 15:25.533
I can certainly see
why Mr. Odom was threatened

15:25.620 --> 15:27.404
by your association
with Mr. Octavio.

15:27.491 --> 15:29.232
That is not true.
That's not what's going on.

15:29.363 --> 15:31.278
Oh, I think it is.

15:31.408 --> 15:34.716
I think that rather than being
Sage's happy fiancée,

15:34.803 --> 15:36.761
you were deeply involved
with both men,

15:36.892 --> 15:38.415
men who were locked
in a violent power struggle

15:38.502 --> 15:40.287
with you at the center.

15:40.417 --> 15:42.463
-None of that is true.
-[Erin] Are you sure?

15:42.593 --> 15:46.554
Might it be that you enjoy
being with dangerous men?

15:46.684 --> 15:48.469
Do you like the attention?

15:48.599 --> 15:50.645
That it was,
in fact, your thing?

15:52.386 --> 15:53.691
No.

15:53.778 --> 15:55.389
Dangerous men like Sage Odom?

15:57.565 --> 15:58.958
No.

15:59.088 --> 16:00.350
Dangerous men like East-O?

16:00.481 --> 16:02.526
[Collette screams]

16:02.657 --> 16:04.441
-No. No.
-[Erin] Now, I think,

16:04.572 --> 16:07.096
in truth, a war was raging
between these two men.

16:07.227 --> 16:08.880
A war that you,
Ms. Jones, started.

16:08.968 --> 16:10.360
A war that led

16:10.491 --> 16:12.754
to an inevitable,
violent showdown

16:12.884 --> 16:15.322
when Sage Odom,
angry and desperate,

16:15.452 --> 16:17.715
took the life
of Ernest Octavio.

16:17.846 --> 16:19.804
Your Honor, is there a question
anytime in our near future?

16:19.891 --> 16:21.763
Oh, yes, yes, there is.
Just one more.

16:23.504 --> 16:28.030
Ms. Jones, on the night
Ernest was killed,

16:28.161 --> 16:30.076
did he threaten
you and Mr. Odom?

16:34.645 --> 16:36.038
May I remind you,
that you are under oath.

16:39.781 --> 16:41.043
Yes.

16:45.221 --> 16:46.309
Yes.

16:46.440 --> 16:49.225
[solemn music plays]

16:49.399 --> 16:51.793
♪ ♪

16:53.229 --> 16:54.578
Nothing further, Your Honor.

16:54.665 --> 16:57.581
[Hooper] Mr. Cruz?

16:57.712 --> 16:59.757
[Cruz] I have no questions
for this witness, Your Honor.

17:03.109 --> 17:04.980
[all] Ms. Baxter!

17:05.111 --> 17:06.677
Well, if what we just saw

17:06.808 --> 17:08.549
was Mr. Odom's strongest
character witness,

17:08.679 --> 17:10.507
then the defense is
in a world of trouble.

17:10.638 --> 17:12.944
-So you think he did it?
-That's what I'm here to prove.

17:13.075 --> 17:14.685
And trust me,
this is just the beginning.

17:14.816 --> 17:16.470
[reporter]
Ms. Baxter, you have filed

17:16.557 --> 17:17.949
to officially enter
the mayoral race.

17:18.080 --> 17:18.733
Do you think
your Republican base is looking

17:18.863 --> 17:20.822
for a conviction here?

17:20.952 --> 17:22.476
I am the district attorney
of this fair city,

17:22.606 --> 17:24.391
and I take
that responsibility seriously.

17:24.521 --> 17:27.437
There is no room for politics
in this courthouse.

17:27.568 --> 17:29.874
Now, if you'll excuse me.
Thank you.

17:30.005 --> 17:32.573
What the fuck was that?
What was she thinking?

17:32.703 --> 17:34.401
Is she out there
for me or for them?

17:34.531 --> 17:36.142
-Fuck.
-[Cruz] That shit was bad.

17:36.272 --> 17:37.360
You-you thought that was bad?
How bad?

17:37.491 --> 17:38.753
-Truthfully?
-Truthfully!

17:38.883 --> 17:39.971
It was a fucking disaster!

17:40.102 --> 17:42.148
Fuck me!

17:42.235 --> 17:44.498
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
Calm down. Calm the fuck down.

17:44.628 --> 17:47.762
Chill, okay?

17:47.849 --> 17:49.111
Level with me, man.
Where we at?

17:49.242 --> 17:50.634
[Cruz] Level with you.

17:50.765 --> 17:53.159
Before today,
I--I liked our odds,

17:53.246 --> 17:54.812
but now that they got
the murder weapon,

17:54.943 --> 17:56.510
and with
that fucking testimony,

17:56.597 --> 17:58.729
I'd say we're at,
I don't know, 50/50.

17:58.816 --> 18:00.688
Fif--ah, fuck.

18:00.818 --> 18:01.819
It doesn't matter.

18:01.950 --> 18:03.386
Fuck, fuck!

18:03.473 --> 18:05.258
Listen, look, I know I said

18:05.388 --> 18:06.302
that I don't wanna
put you on the stand,

18:06.389 --> 18:07.782
but we're gonna have to do it.

18:07.912 --> 18:10.001
Yes. Yes, let's fucking do it.

18:10.132 --> 18:12.091
-Let's do it.
-All right, good.

18:12.221 --> 18:14.658
'Cause after Collette,
your testimony could be

18:14.789 --> 18:17.226
the most important thing
we present right now.

18:17.357 --> 18:19.272
I'm gonna put you up
first thing tomorrow morning,

18:19.402 --> 18:20.621
but we might
have to play rough.

18:23.102 --> 18:24.842
Whatever the fuck we gotta do,

18:24.929 --> 18:26.627
just fucking do it.

18:28.019 --> 18:30.631
["Played My Heart" playing]

18:30.805 --> 18:33.590
♪ ♪

18:33.764 --> 18:36.202
[singer] ♪ Open eyes
In the night ♪

18:36.376 --> 18:39.379
♪ You find me ♪

18:39.553 --> 18:42.164
♪ Don't know where to begin ♪

18:42.338 --> 18:45.298
♪ This time ♪

18:45.472 --> 18:48.257
♪ Shadows always overwrite ♪

18:48.431 --> 18:51.260
♪ What once were lies ♪

18:51.434 --> 18:52.827
♪ Now I know ♪

18:53.001 --> 18:55.699
♪ This is where you say ♪

18:58.137 --> 19:03.707
♪ You played my heart again ♪

19:03.881 --> 19:09.104
♪ Now I'm laying
With the enemy ♪

19:09.887 --> 19:15.719
♪ You played it all away ♪

19:15.893 --> 19:17.678
♪ Now I can see the web ♪

19:17.765 --> 19:20.376
♪ That you're spinning
In front of me ♪

19:20.550 --> 19:23.292
♪ ♪

19:31.344 --> 19:33.476
The hell is this
supposed to be?

19:33.607 --> 19:35.043
It's a grant of immunity.

19:35.174 --> 19:36.871
It allows you to testify

19:37.001 --> 19:38.612
without incriminating
yourself.

19:38.742 --> 19:40.135
I already told you
I'm not doing this.

19:40.266 --> 19:42.703
You get me to trial.
You tip this in for me.

19:42.833 --> 19:45.836
So you're going to do this,
or else.

19:45.967 --> 19:47.708
Or else what?

19:47.838 --> 19:49.449
You either get up on the stand

19:49.579 --> 19:51.799
and you say
what I need you to say,

19:51.929 --> 19:53.888
or I will see to it
that you are locked away

19:54.018 --> 19:55.803
for a very long time,

19:55.890 --> 20:00.111
where, I might add, you belong.

20:00.199 --> 20:01.678
If I get up on that stand,

20:01.809 --> 20:03.202
I'm not gonna last
a day out here.

20:03.332 --> 20:04.725
Well...

20:07.293 --> 20:08.903
You should ask yourself
this, then.

20:09.033 --> 20:12.341
[tense music plays]

20:12.472 --> 20:14.082
How long will you last
in county jail

20:14.213 --> 20:16.215
when I violate your ass
back there

20:16.302 --> 20:18.695
and then let it slip

20:18.826 --> 20:21.785
that we've been having
these little firesides chats?

20:21.916 --> 20:23.047
Fuck you.

20:25.528 --> 20:28.270
The feeling is mutual.

20:28.401 --> 20:30.794
So you be very fucking careful
what you say next.

20:33.319 --> 20:35.103
Do we have a deal?

20:35.277 --> 20:38.019
♪ ♪

20:44.852 --> 20:46.157
Man, whatever.

20:46.288 --> 20:47.855
"Whatever." Is that a yes?

20:47.942 --> 20:49.117
Yes.

20:49.248 --> 20:51.859
[Erin] Excellent.

20:51.989 --> 20:53.556
See you in court.

20:57.081 --> 20:59.127
And wear a suit.

20:59.214 --> 21:00.084
If you have one, that is.

21:08.267 --> 21:10.007
-[door closes]
-Man, there you are.

21:10.138 --> 21:11.444
Man, I've been trying
to call you and everything.

21:11.574 --> 21:13.054
Where you been?

21:13.184 --> 21:16.231
Wait, w-what's all this?
What's going on?

21:16.362 --> 21:18.755
I need to get out of town
for a little bit.

21:18.886 --> 21:21.454
Okay.
[scoffs]

21:21.584 --> 21:23.325
Okay, is this about
what I said to you at the club?

21:23.456 --> 21:25.240
Nigga, why you care?

21:25.371 --> 21:26.546
It ain't like
you gon' miss me much.

21:26.676 --> 21:28.939
[Rigo]
Look, man, I'm sorry, a'ight?

21:29.070 --> 21:30.680
Damn--what I said
was out of pocket, a'ight?

21:30.811 --> 21:31.942
I was bugging,
but a nigga had just put

21:32.029 --> 21:33.161
a whole gun in my face, a'ight?

21:33.292 --> 21:34.945
I was mad as hell.

21:35.076 --> 21:36.599
I said some shit
in the heat of the moment.

21:36.730 --> 21:38.688
I'm sorry.
Damn, cut me some slack. Shit.

21:38.819 --> 21:40.429
Plus we got some work
to do anyway, bruh,

21:40.560 --> 21:42.301
[clears throat]

21:42.431 --> 21:43.954
starting with this.

21:49.569 --> 21:51.179
The fuck is this for?

21:51.310 --> 21:54.225
I put your name
on the publishing contract.

21:54.313 --> 21:56.706
This is your first
royalty check, player.

21:56.793 --> 21:58.708
Yes, sir.

21:58.839 --> 22:00.014
And there's plenty more
where that came from.

22:02.625 --> 22:03.974
What, man?
I just did you a whole solid.

22:04.105 --> 22:05.541
-What's up?
-This ain't it, dawg.

22:07.151 --> 22:08.675
Then what is?

22:08.805 --> 22:11.068
DA trying to put me
on the stand.

22:11.199 --> 22:12.853
Fuck.

22:12.983 --> 22:16.552
Yo, dawg, if I do this shit...

22:16.683 --> 22:18.337
man, the streets is coming,

22:21.035 --> 22:22.950
Then don't.

22:23.080 --> 22:24.908
Okay, and if I don't,
the DA coming for me instead.

22:24.995 --> 22:28.521
She's trying to lock me back up
if I don't testify.

22:28.608 --> 22:31.306
A'ight, cool.
So this is what we do.

22:31.437 --> 22:33.177
You do it.

22:33.308 --> 22:34.875
Testify, bruh.

22:35.005 --> 22:37.791
If Sage get sent up,
the world is ours, bruh.

22:37.921 --> 22:39.401
The whole tour,
the recording contracts,

22:39.532 --> 22:41.360
the money, everything.

22:41.490 --> 22:42.361
Dawg, that check, that's just
the beginning, bruh.

22:42.491 --> 22:43.405
Rigo, but what I'm saying--

22:43.536 --> 22:45.929
But--but nothing.

22:46.060 --> 22:48.932
'Quise, all you gotta do is
say the same thing I'ma say.

22:49.063 --> 22:51.413
That gun?
Shit, I ain't never seen it.

22:53.328 --> 22:56.766
Uh, Sage?
He's a bad fucking guy.

22:56.897 --> 22:58.942
'Quise, all you gotta do is
just fall in line with this.

22:59.029 --> 23:01.684
Fall in line with me.
A'ight? This shit'll work.

23:01.815 --> 23:04.861
Rigo, it's no way I'm not
getting touched if I do this.

23:04.992 --> 23:07.037
Touched by who?

23:07.124 --> 23:08.909
Dawg, we can have security
taking care of all this shit

23:09.039 --> 23:11.999
while we in LA chillin', bruh.

23:12.129 --> 23:14.741
Living a life above
all this bullshit, man.

23:14.871 --> 23:15.959
I don't know.

23:16.090 --> 23:19.398
'Quise, when I say I got you,

23:19.528 --> 23:21.312
I got you, bruh.
I ain't playing.

23:23.358 --> 23:24.620
Listen, tomorrow,
we put Sage away.

23:26.579 --> 23:28.102
What's up?

23:28.232 --> 23:31.018
[soft music plays]

23:31.148 --> 23:32.672
[sighs]

23:32.759 --> 23:36.284
A'ight. I'll do it.

23:36.415 --> 23:38.155
I don't have nowhere else
to go anyway, so...

23:40.941 --> 23:43.596
My brother, my brother.

23:43.726 --> 23:45.206
[chuckles]
Fuck Sage.

23:49.471 --> 23:53.127
So you grew up with East-O.
Were you friends?

23:53.257 --> 23:55.782
Ah, yeah, something like that.

23:55.912 --> 23:57.784
Uh, same neighborhood,
different situations.

23:57.914 --> 23:59.568
Uh, as far as East,

23:59.699 --> 24:02.005
slightly more harsh
circumstance,

24:02.136 --> 24:03.616
if you know what I mean.

24:03.746 --> 24:05.269
Yet you became
business partners.

24:05.400 --> 24:07.228
[Sage] Something like that.

24:07.358 --> 24:10.013
Okay, s-so East-O thought
he was a producer.

24:10.100 --> 24:11.972
It was never gonna happen,
but he did know

24:12.102 --> 24:14.104
a lot of the right people,
and he wasn't shy

24:14.235 --> 24:16.063
about, you know,
throwing his weight around.

24:16.193 --> 24:19.022
And I was a nobody at the time,
so benefited both of us.

24:19.153 --> 24:22.069
And eventually, you, uh,
you parted ways.

24:22.199 --> 24:24.680
Yeah, so my music takes off,

24:24.811 --> 24:27.509
I leave Atlanta,
and we lost contact after that.

24:27.640 --> 24:30.294
I went one way and I guess
you could say he went another.

24:30.425 --> 24:32.993
[Cruz] And uh, like East-O,

24:33.080 --> 24:35.648
you also grew up with
your current business partner,

24:35.735 --> 24:37.563
Ms. Collette Jones,
is that correct?

24:37.650 --> 24:39.086
[Sage] Yes, yes. That is true.

24:39.216 --> 24:41.654
Just young kids
chasing a dream.

24:41.784 --> 24:44.265
Uh, but if I may correct you,
I would not call

24:44.395 --> 24:46.572
Ms. Collette Jones
my business partner.

24:46.702 --> 24:50.358
[Cruz] No?
Well, what would you call her?

24:50.489 --> 24:52.926
[Sage] More of an assistant.

24:53.056 --> 24:55.319
You see, on my way up,
I reached down and grabbed

24:55.406 --> 24:57.060
as many of my people
as I could,

24:57.191 --> 24:58.627
and Collette was no exception.

24:58.714 --> 25:00.324
She was a backup dancer
of mine

25:00.455 --> 25:02.544
with some real promise,

25:02.675 --> 25:05.721
but then--tragic accident
ended her career.

25:05.852 --> 25:08.071
I felt sorry for her.

25:08.202 --> 25:10.291
So I set her up at my school.

25:10.421 --> 25:13.947
[Cruz] So Ms. Jones is not
in charge of High Water.

25:14.077 --> 25:16.863
[Sage, echoing]
No. I run High Water.

25:16.993 --> 25:18.299
I make all the decisions.

25:18.429 --> 25:19.735
[Cruz] Hmm.

25:19.866 --> 25:21.694
Now, were you aware

25:21.824 --> 25:23.130
that Collette was sleeping
with East-O?

25:23.260 --> 25:25.262
[Sage] No. No, I wasn't at all.

25:25.393 --> 25:27.961
Listen, I'm a very busy man.
Okay? I'm an entertainer.

25:28.091 --> 25:30.180
A lot of moving parts
in my life.

25:30.311 --> 25:31.573
Got no time to worry about
what my secretary is doing

25:31.704 --> 25:32.574
in her personal life.

25:32.661 --> 25:33.706
Not my concern.

25:33.836 --> 25:35.838
But you're engaged, aren't you?

25:35.969 --> 25:38.232
Yes, but that aspect
of our personal life

25:38.319 --> 25:40.495
didn't start
until after East-O died.

25:40.626 --> 25:43.629
And I wouldn't hold the past
against her.

25:43.716 --> 25:45.805
[Cruz] Of course not.

25:45.892 --> 25:48.329
So jealousy was never a factor
in your relationship.

25:48.459 --> 25:50.113
Jealous of who?

25:50.244 --> 25:52.376
Yeah, no, no.
It's not how I roll.

25:52.463 --> 25:55.162
That's not how you roll.

25:55.292 --> 25:57.556
Now, I'd like to turn
our attention

25:57.686 --> 25:58.731
to the murder weapon.

26:01.864 --> 26:03.866
Your Honor.

26:03.997 --> 26:07.000
Mr. Odom,
have you seen this gun before?

26:07.087 --> 26:10.307
In fact, I have.
Uh, not for some time.

26:10.438 --> 26:13.180
Uh, that gun was a gift
that I gave to East-O

26:13.310 --> 26:14.573
when I left Atlanta
for my first tour.

26:14.703 --> 26:16.836
But it was registered to you?

26:16.966 --> 26:18.794
Probably something
I should've taken care.

26:18.925 --> 26:20.491
I-I honestly didn't know
I had to at the time.

26:20.622 --> 26:23.320
However, not my gun.

26:23.451 --> 26:24.974
Thank you.

26:25.105 --> 26:26.933
[Hooper]
Ms. Baxter, your witness.

26:28.108 --> 26:30.545
[Erin] Let's talk about
Ernest Octavio, shall we?

26:30.632 --> 26:34.070
So you're insisting that
your relationship deteriorated

26:34.201 --> 26:35.550
quite some time
before his death.

26:35.681 --> 26:37.596
Yes. Yes, I am.

26:37.726 --> 26:40.555
Can you describe
what we're looking at here?

26:43.427 --> 26:45.255
[Sage] Yes, that is me

26:45.386 --> 26:47.040
in a rather fly jacket,
if I do say so myself.

26:47.127 --> 26:48.781
I gotta find that.

26:48.911 --> 26:51.174
Oh, and--and East-O
at a local strip club.

26:51.261 --> 26:53.394
So does that mean
you're lying, Mr. Odom?

26:53.524 --> 26:55.483
[Sage] Uh, no. I'm a celebrity.

26:55.614 --> 26:57.528
People run up on me
all the time when I'm out.

26:57.659 --> 26:59.356
Would it surprise you if I said

26:59.443 --> 27:01.228
that I had
a number of witnesses

27:01.315 --> 27:04.231
that could place
Ernest Octavio at your school

27:04.361 --> 27:06.625
on multiple occasions
just prior to his murder?

27:06.755 --> 27:08.496
That wouldn't surprise me
at all, to be honest.

27:08.627 --> 27:11.020
Uh, his son was a student
at my school.

27:11.151 --> 27:12.500
Look, I know
what you're trying to do,

27:12.631 --> 27:14.720
but I had no business
with East-O.

27:14.807 --> 27:17.026
That is a lie,

27:17.157 --> 27:20.073
just like you lied about your
relationship with Ms. Jones.

27:20.160 --> 27:22.597
She is, in fact,
instrumental to your business,

27:22.728 --> 27:24.251
to your school,
and to your career,

27:24.381 --> 27:25.687
and all the while,
she was having an affair

27:25.818 --> 27:27.907
with Mr. Octavio
behind your back.

27:28.037 --> 27:29.865
That threatened you,
didn't it?

27:29.952 --> 27:32.215
That threatened everything
that you have built.

27:32.346 --> 27:34.609
Look, I had no beef...

27:34.740 --> 27:36.306
-Oh.
-With East-O, okay?

27:36.437 --> 27:39.440
Come on, the guy was a nobody.
Come on.

27:39.570 --> 27:41.703
[Erin] Does this look like
two people who--

27:41.834 --> 27:43.705
how did you put it--
have no beef?

27:45.315 --> 27:47.883
[dramatic music plays]

27:48.057 --> 27:50.973
♪ ♪

27:51.104 --> 27:53.236
No, in fact,

27:53.367 --> 27:56.326
you and Ernest Octavio
were mortal enemies.

27:56.457 --> 27:58.589
It's why you publicly
humiliated his son Rigo

27:58.720 --> 28:00.200
and kicked him
out of your school.

28:00.287 --> 28:01.854
That was an act
of pure revenge.

28:01.984 --> 28:03.943
Come on!

28:04.073 --> 28:05.945
The kid is currently
headlining my world tour.

28:06.075 --> 28:08.164
[Erin] And that's because every
step you took with that boy

28:08.251 --> 28:09.775
was designed
to humiliate Ernest,

28:09.905 --> 28:12.038
and Ernest hated you for it.

28:12.168 --> 28:13.996
Your Honor, the prosecution
is badgering the witness.

28:14.083 --> 28:16.303
He hated you
because you left him behind,

28:16.433 --> 28:18.261
like you did to Collette,
like you did to Rigo,

28:18.392 --> 28:19.828
like you did to so many people
in your life

28:19.959 --> 28:22.570
because that, Mr. Odom,
is how you roll.

28:22.657 --> 28:24.180
-Judge.
-[Hooper] Ms. Baxter.

28:24.311 --> 28:25.573
[Erin] And when Ernest
finally came after you,

28:25.704 --> 28:26.443
you felt threatened didn't you?

28:26.530 --> 28:28.228
Didn't you?

28:28.315 --> 28:30.447
So you took your gun,
the gun that you owned,

28:30.578 --> 28:32.667
the gun that was registered
to you, and you shot him.

28:32.798 --> 28:34.843
You killed him.

28:34.974 --> 28:37.063
Get the fuck
out of my face, bitch!

28:37.193 --> 28:38.760
-[courtroom murmurs]
-I didn't fucking kill nobody!

28:38.891 --> 28:39.674
I ain't got time
to kill nobody.

28:39.805 --> 28:41.110
I'm a goddamn celebrity.

28:41.241 --> 28:43.939
[courtroom muttering]

28:44.070 --> 28:47.203
[Hooper]
That's enough, Mr. Odom.

28:47.334 --> 28:48.639
You may step down.

28:48.814 --> 28:51.599
♪ ♪

28:57.692 --> 29:00.477
[intense hip-hop plays]

29:00.564 --> 29:04.090
♪ ♪

29:05.308 --> 29:08.224
[Erin] Rigo, you're
the opening act on Sage's tour.

29:08.355 --> 29:10.139
You were a student
at his school.

29:10.270 --> 29:12.533
You must have a pretty good
sense of who he is.

29:12.663 --> 29:15.971
Sure. Sage is very talented.

29:16.102 --> 29:18.713
But, uh, he's not the person
everybody thinks he is.

29:18.844 --> 29:20.628
He selfish as--

29:22.543 --> 29:23.979
Let's just say, uh,

29:24.110 --> 29:26.329
Sage only looks out
for himself.

29:26.460 --> 29:28.462
[Erin] And he kicked you
out of High Water?

29:28.549 --> 29:30.943
You said something that day
that made Sage mad, didn't you?

29:31.030 --> 29:32.988
I said he was using me

29:33.119 --> 29:36.035
just like my pops
back in the day,

29:36.165 --> 29:37.079
and that really set him off.

29:37.210 --> 29:39.081
And why is that?

29:39.168 --> 29:40.909
That's because
in the beginnin',

29:41.040 --> 29:42.781
my dad made Sage.

29:42.911 --> 29:44.565
[whispering]
Do you hear this bullshit?

29:44.695 --> 29:46.567
[Rigo] My dad put Sage
in front of the right people

29:46.697 --> 29:48.221
back in the day
when they first started.

29:48.351 --> 29:50.005
And he would have been
a great producer too

29:50.136 --> 29:50.397
if Sage would've gave him
half the chance.

29:52.791 --> 29:55.532
But Sage don't like sharing
the spotlight with anybody.

29:55.663 --> 29:57.360
He's selfish like that
about everything.

29:57.491 --> 30:01.451
His music,
his school, his dance...

30:01.582 --> 30:03.497
and especially Collette.

30:03.627 --> 30:05.281
[Erin] Collette?

30:05.412 --> 30:07.631
But Sage has testified
that he didn't know

30:07.762 --> 30:09.720
about your father's history
with Collette.

30:09.808 --> 30:11.722
-That's a lie.
-Oh.

30:11.853 --> 30:14.813
Sage knew all along
about her and my dad, a'ight?

30:14.900 --> 30:16.510
Their relationship
pissed him off.

30:16.640 --> 30:18.991
Well, that doesn't sound
like a man that didn't care.

30:19.121 --> 30:20.427
That sounds like
an obsessed man.

30:20.557 --> 30:22.429
That sounds like an angry man.

30:22.559 --> 30:25.171
Nigga, he is.
We literally all just saw it.

30:26.912 --> 30:29.088
Yes, we did.

30:29.218 --> 30:31.960
Now, you were close
with your father.

30:32.091 --> 30:34.049
You lived with him
your whole life.

30:34.180 --> 30:37.879
Now, Sage claims that
he gifted this to your father.

30:39.925 --> 30:42.318
-Have you ever seen it?
-This friend?

30:42.405 --> 30:43.537
This was the friend
that had your back

30:43.667 --> 30:45.191
when nobody else did.

30:45.278 --> 30:47.323
What you doing here?

30:47.454 --> 30:50.152
[solemn music plays]

30:50.326 --> 30:51.632
♪ ♪

30:51.762 --> 30:54.026
No. No, I have not.

30:54.156 --> 30:55.984
[clears throat]

30:56.115 --> 30:58.508
[Erin] Thank you.
Just one more question.

30:58.639 --> 31:02.251
Do you believe that Sage Odom
killed your father?

31:02.382 --> 31:04.340
I do,

31:04.471 --> 31:05.951
and I also believe
he would've killed me

31:06.081 --> 31:07.343
that night
he was beating my ass too

31:07.474 --> 31:09.128
if someone
didn't pull him off me.

31:13.175 --> 31:16.004
Thank you. Nothing further.

31:16.135 --> 31:17.353
[Cruz] May I, Your Honor?
[clears throat]

31:18.746 --> 31:19.747
Let's get this straight.

31:19.834 --> 31:21.488
This is the man

31:21.575 --> 31:23.359
that you're opening for
on tour, yes or no?

31:23.446 --> 31:25.274
Yeah, but I didn't want to.

31:25.405 --> 31:27.059
I--if I wouldn't have,
Sage would have ruined me.

31:27.189 --> 31:29.409
Tell you the truth,

31:29.539 --> 31:31.367
I only did the tour
for Collette.

31:31.498 --> 31:34.153
[Cruz] Hmm. Yeah, well,
that's very easy to say.

31:34.283 --> 31:36.285
But the fact is, it was Sage

31:36.372 --> 31:38.026
who put you on his tour,

31:38.157 --> 31:40.724
and you are still
reaping the benefits.

31:40.811 --> 31:42.335
You didn't drop out of the
tour after Sage was accused

31:42.465 --> 31:43.814
of killing your father,
did you?

31:43.902 --> 31:45.468
It wasn't about Sage
at that point.

31:45.555 --> 31:48.602
Like I said,
it was about Collette.

31:48.732 --> 31:50.256
She was the only one
who believed in me.

31:52.432 --> 31:54.216
[sighs]

31:54.347 --> 31:57.089
Collette believed in me
all along,

31:57.219 --> 31:59.308
even when I didn't believe
in my own damn self.

31:59.439 --> 32:01.528
And I love her for that.

32:01.615 --> 32:02.964
Like, she sees me.

32:06.315 --> 32:07.969
Everything I did,
from the moment I stepped foot

32:08.056 --> 32:09.275
at High Water, I did for her.

32:12.626 --> 32:15.890
[Cruz] Your Honor,
it's Sage's school.

32:16.021 --> 32:19.111
It's Sage's tour.
Sage calls all the shots.

32:19.241 --> 32:20.895
-No.
-Hmm.

32:21.026 --> 32:22.549
Sage said a whole lot of stuff
about Collette

32:22.679 --> 32:24.986
just being an employee there,
but nah.

32:25.117 --> 32:26.988
Collette is High Water.

32:27.119 --> 32:28.947
She's the only one
who looked out for me.

32:29.077 --> 32:30.339
The only one who looked out
for all of us.

32:30.470 --> 32:32.080
-Okay--
-No, let me finish.

32:32.211 --> 32:34.430
Well, then finish.

32:34.517 --> 32:37.129
Colette saw a talent in me.

32:37.259 --> 32:39.522
She knew
what I was capable of.

32:39.653 --> 32:40.871
Just like my dad.

32:45.180 --> 32:48.227
All my dad ever wanted from me
was to be something better.

32:48.357 --> 32:50.707
To be legit.

32:50.838 --> 32:52.579
[chuckles]

32:52.709 --> 32:56.061
That's why he came at you
so hard, man.

32:56.191 --> 32:59.542
But you... you weren't
worried about nothin'

32:59.673 --> 33:01.240
but your own damn self.

33:01.414 --> 33:04.156
♪ ♪

33:14.514 --> 33:18.257
Your Honor,
I think we could use a recess.

33:18.387 --> 33:19.823
[Hooper] Agreed, Mr. Cruz?

33:22.435 --> 33:24.785
Agreed.

33:24.915 --> 33:27.614
[Hooper]
Then let's resume tomorrow.

33:27.701 --> 33:29.094
[gavel taps]

33:31.792 --> 33:34.490
[background chatter]

33:34.621 --> 33:36.144
[Magic] My man.

33:36.275 --> 33:37.841
Yo, yo.

33:37.972 --> 33:39.800
Yo, you good?

33:39.930 --> 33:43.847
Pssh. I ain't gonna lie.
Turn in the hole sucks.

33:43.934 --> 33:45.414
But I'm good.

33:45.545 --> 33:47.373
Yo, I'm--I'm sorry, man.
I told--I told--

33:47.503 --> 33:50.941
No, no, no, man.
It's cool, bruh.

33:51.072 --> 33:53.248
You didn't know any better,
and I wasn't about to let

33:53.379 --> 33:54.597
that big motherfucker
fuck with you.

33:56.469 --> 33:57.644
How you doing?

34:00.212 --> 34:01.691
The fancy lawyer
ain't cutting it?

34:01.822 --> 34:03.693
Nah, that ain't it.

34:03.824 --> 34:05.652
This shit just not going
the way it supposed to, man.

34:05.782 --> 34:09.395
I--I--I fucked my testimony up.
I let the fucking DA get to me.

34:09.525 --> 34:11.223
That's what she wants.

34:11.353 --> 34:13.529
And when they poke at you
like that,

34:13.616 --> 34:16.663
you gotta button up
and just take that shit.

34:16.750 --> 34:19.057
Look, please excuse me
if I don't feel like

34:19.187 --> 34:21.102
kissing somebody ass right now.

34:21.233 --> 34:23.148
You know and I know

34:23.278 --> 34:25.585
that most of these
motherfuckers is bullshit.

34:25.715 --> 34:28.805
But in the case of me,
I really didn't do it, dawg.

34:28.936 --> 34:30.807
[Magic] It don't matter.

34:30.938 --> 34:32.287
You think
you the first motherfucker

34:32.374 --> 34:34.681
to walk in here
that shouldn't be?

34:34.811 --> 34:36.813
Sometimes that's just
how shit goes.

34:36.944 --> 34:38.902
A brother gets caught up,
ends up in here,

34:39.033 --> 34:41.079
and the system goes to work.

34:41.166 --> 34:43.037
And once you're in it,
hard as fuck to get out.

34:50.044 --> 34:53.134
No cap, I'm scared, dawg.

34:55.832 --> 34:58.444
-I...
-[Magic] No, no, no, no, no.

34:58.574 --> 34:59.401
I don't know
if I can do this shit, man.

34:59.532 --> 35:01.490
Stay positive.

35:01.577 --> 35:04.363
Come on. It ain't over.

35:04.493 --> 35:05.755
Things'll work out.

35:08.541 --> 35:09.977
It can happen.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.413
What if it don't?

35:15.330 --> 35:17.550
Then I'll be here
when you get back.

35:17.637 --> 35:20.422
[soft music plays]

35:20.596 --> 35:23.338
♪ ♪

35:32.304 --> 35:34.958
I'm sorry, man.

35:35.089 --> 35:37.787
I'm sorry about what happened
at the school...

35:40.007 --> 35:41.487
All of it, man, I--

35:43.793 --> 35:45.839
I'ma make it up to you.

35:45.969 --> 35:50.322
A'ight, someway, somehow,

35:50.452 --> 35:53.063
I'ma do right by you.

35:53.194 --> 35:56.023
'Preciate you. I really do.

35:59.505 --> 36:01.028
Good luck tomorrow.

36:04.205 --> 36:06.860
And believe me when I say,

36:06.990 --> 36:08.427
I hope I never see you again.

36:08.514 --> 36:11.256
♪ ♪

36:20.003 --> 36:22.745
[thunder rumbling]

36:32.407 --> 36:34.366
Are you fucking kidding me?
I'm making us dinner.

36:34.453 --> 36:37.412
Come on, Poppy,
I'm hungry, a'ight?

36:37.543 --> 36:40.328
Which is why
I'm making us dinner.

36:40.415 --> 36:41.938
Well, don't.

36:42.069 --> 36:44.114
Order some takeout
or some shit.

36:44.245 --> 36:46.291
You are such an asshole,
you know that?

36:46.421 --> 36:48.380
[Rigo] Poppy, will you get off
my fucking back, please?

36:48.510 --> 36:50.120
A'ight?
I don't know if you could tell,

36:50.251 --> 36:52.384
but I had
a really long fucking day.

36:52.514 --> 36:54.212
What the fuck is up
with you and Collette?

36:55.909 --> 36:57.911
Is there something
I need to know?

36:57.998 --> 37:00.740
Oh, my God, how many times we
gotta go over this shit, Poppy?

37:00.870 --> 37:02.437
Look, we are gonna get ours,

37:02.568 --> 37:04.831
but in the meantime,
we need Collette.

37:04.961 --> 37:07.703
-Do we, though? Do we really?
-Yeah.

37:07.790 --> 37:09.836
Who gonna run the tour, huh?
Me? What, are you gonna run it?

37:12.447 --> 37:14.710
Exactly.
Look, as long as Sage is gone,

37:14.841 --> 37:17.235
she's the one who's gonna make
shit go around, a'ight?

37:17.365 --> 37:19.585
Then maybe she's all you need.

37:19.672 --> 37:21.630
Yeah, maybe I should just
get the fuck out of here.

37:21.761 --> 37:24.764
[Rigo] Oh, my God!
Will you stop it? Damn!

37:24.894 --> 37:26.418
Poppy, there's nothing going on
with me and Collette.

37:26.548 --> 37:28.550
It doesn't feel like
nothing, Rigo.

37:28.681 --> 37:31.074
Look, a'ight, look, I may need
Collette right now, okay,

37:31.205 --> 37:32.946
but I can't do this shit
without you, Poppy.

37:33.076 --> 37:34.252
I can't. I won't.

37:37.124 --> 37:40.258
What is this really about?
Hmm? Hmm?

37:40.388 --> 37:42.390
Is it about Marquise?

37:42.521 --> 37:44.174
[Poppy] I sacrificed everything
for you,

37:44.262 --> 37:46.481
and it's like
you never really listen to me,

37:46.612 --> 37:48.527
not about anything
and definitely not about him.

37:48.614 --> 37:49.876
[Rigo] He's my brother.

37:50.006 --> 37:51.704
[Poppy] I don't fucking care.

37:51.791 --> 37:52.705
Who-who-who knows
if that's really true?

37:52.792 --> 37:53.793
[Rigo] Poppy, come on.

37:53.923 --> 37:55.708
We had a plan.

37:55.838 --> 37:57.753
So I sacrificed for you.
I burned bridges for you.

37:57.884 --> 37:59.407
I thought this was
about me and you.

37:59.538 --> 38:00.408
Poppy, it is.

38:00.539 --> 38:02.802
Then show me.

38:02.932 --> 38:04.369
You know what? Fuck it.

38:05.718 --> 38:06.545
Fuck Marquise.

38:08.938 --> 38:10.244
All right?
I'll let that shit go.

38:10.375 --> 38:13.334
[tense music plays]

38:13.421 --> 38:15.293
♪ ♪

38:15.423 --> 38:17.033
You would you really do that?

38:17.164 --> 38:19.253
Yes.

38:19.384 --> 38:20.559
We just leave him behind,
a'ight?

38:20.689 --> 38:22.474
It'll just be you and me.

38:22.648 --> 38:25.433
♪ ♪

38:30.786 --> 38:33.833
[announcer] All the passengers
for Charlotte North Carolina

38:33.963 --> 38:34.703
we will be departing in ten
minutes.

38:37.184 --> 38:38.098
Hey.

38:40.013 --> 38:40.927
Thanks for coming.

38:45.410 --> 38:47.150
What's going on?

38:47.281 --> 38:49.196
Shit went a little sideways

38:49.327 --> 38:51.503
and, uh, I gotta
get out of Atlanta tonight.

38:52.982 --> 38:54.767
What you mean?

38:54.897 --> 38:56.769
I didn't wanna leave
without saying goodbye.

38:56.899 --> 38:58.858
Then don't.

38:58.988 --> 39:02.296
Marquise, what happened?
Let me help.

39:02.427 --> 39:04.342
You can't.

39:04.472 --> 39:07.649
There really ain't nothing
anybody can do about it.

39:07.780 --> 39:09.651
I've done a lot of shit--

39:09.738 --> 39:10.913
a lot of shit I'm not proud of.

39:11.000 --> 39:12.045
I know something about that.

39:12.175 --> 39:13.438
You can tell me anything.

39:13.568 --> 39:14.874
I can handle it. Trust me.

39:14.961 --> 39:16.049
I'm just not the person
you think I am.

39:17.355 --> 39:19.444
[thunder rumbles]

39:22.708 --> 39:25.537
We may be from
different countries, Marquise,

39:25.667 --> 39:28.191
but we're from the same place.

39:28.322 --> 39:29.845
I'm not a Scorpio rising.

39:32.370 --> 39:35.634
-I'm-I'm not following.
-My tattoo.

39:35.764 --> 39:37.549
I didn't choose
the artwork or the ink.

39:40.378 --> 39:42.336
My brother and my family
needed protection.

39:44.686 --> 39:46.645
It's a gang tat, Marquise.

39:50.126 --> 39:51.171
Don't let the name fool you.

39:51.301 --> 39:52.477
I'm no angel.

39:55.044 --> 39:56.611
So you gonna tell me
what's going on?

40:04.445 --> 40:06.273
Before you and I met...

40:08.623 --> 40:10.495
I was locked up in jail.

40:12.235 --> 40:14.977
Made a shitty decision
to get out.

40:16.892 --> 40:19.852
I snitched.

40:19.982 --> 40:21.897
It's either I'm going back
to jail or I'm fucked forever,

40:22.028 --> 40:23.899
so I gotta run.

40:23.986 --> 40:26.380
-Where?
-I don't know.

40:26.511 --> 40:30.123
Seem like everywhere I go,
trouble find me.

40:30.253 --> 40:34.127
I can't escape it.
It's like... my dad was in it.

40:34.214 --> 40:36.434
[solemn music plays]

40:36.564 --> 40:39.785
I guess it's just who I am too.

40:39.915 --> 40:41.613
That's not true.

40:41.700 --> 40:45.007
♪ ♪

40:45.704 --> 40:47.749
The thing no one tells you
about running

40:47.880 --> 40:51.449
is, no matter where you run to,
you'll still be there.

40:51.579 --> 40:53.929
So you can run if you want,

40:54.016 --> 40:55.496
but you better be
running towards something

40:55.627 --> 40:59.369
and not just away
from your life.

40:59.500 --> 41:01.154
C'mon baby, I want you
to come with me.

41:05.767 --> 41:07.334
You're a good person.

41:09.728 --> 41:10.903
I see that.

41:14.036 --> 41:15.821
Don't be afraid to show
that side of you

41:15.951 --> 41:17.692
to other people or to yourself.

41:17.823 --> 41:21.435
[dramatic music plays]

41:21.566 --> 41:23.785
But I gave up on running.

41:23.916 --> 41:26.179
I can't come with you.

41:26.353 --> 41:29.095
♪ ♪

41:29.225 --> 41:30.836
And I don't like goodbyes.

41:36.885 --> 41:40.106
♪ ♪

41:46.329 --> 41:50.769
♪ ♪

42:03.129 --> 42:05.914
[R&B music plays]

42:06.088 --> 42:09.614
♪ ♪

42:09.744 --> 42:13.574
[Rigo] Tell me you didn't feel
what I felt up on that stage.

42:13.705 --> 42:15.445
Hey, this is what
you were meant to do.

42:15.620 --> 42:16.969
♪ Hey ♪

42:17.143 --> 42:19.580
♪ Nobody said it would be ♪

42:19.754 --> 42:22.017
♪ Happy ever after
With you and me ♪

42:22.191 --> 42:23.889
♪ But I'm riding ♪

42:24.063 --> 42:25.978
♪ And that's a guarantee ♪

42:26.065 --> 42:29.068
♪ Ain't no telling your story
Without me ♪

42:29.242 --> 42:30.678
♪ I won't act like it's easy ♪

42:30.852 --> 42:32.854
♪ You know
That wouldn't be true ♪

42:32.941 --> 42:35.988
♪ I can't act like I don't want
To smack the shit out of you ♪

42:36.075 --> 42:38.860
♪ Sometimes, I can act like
You don't give me the blues ♪

42:39.034 --> 42:40.993
♪ But I can't act like
There ain't nothing ♪

42:41.167 --> 42:43.212
♪ That I wouldn't do
For you, baby ♪

42:43.386 --> 42:45.388
♪ It might sound crazy ♪

42:45.563 --> 42:48.609
